                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_109253">Drayton</placeName>.

                        <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Scop</surname>
                        </persName> in the new land of <placeName key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName>, grants to <persName nymRef="Scop">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Scop">
                           <forename>Emma</forename>
                        </persName> his sisters all right he might have hereditarily in land which fell to <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Scop</surname>
                        </persName> in <placeName key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName>, and a messuage by <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> of <surname>Knoston</surname>
                        </persName>’s ‘placea’. 
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">fitz-Philip</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Simon</forename> de <surname>aula</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> de <surname>pistrina</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   Thomas le ..., 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Godchep</surname>
                        </persName>. 
   <origDate notBefore="1300" notAfter="1320" precision="low">
                           <supplied>c. 1300–20.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
